book_description: Two sisters, made miserable by the treatment of a puritanical father find, as they fondly believe, freedom in marriage. They find instead bitter disillusion, the one because of her husband's cruelty, the other because of her own wayward and wilful selfishness. But in the end happiness comes to them, as it has a way of doing when people face up to facts and take a strong hold of themselves.
